    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-05-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-05-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="372"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d372">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">French minister for foreign
                            affairs</gloss> to Mr. <persName type="to">Cambon</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram presented by the French ambassador to the
                        President, May 12, 1902.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-05-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 11, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Thank the Government of the United States for the sympathy evidenced by the
                    American people. It will never be forgotten in France.</p>
                <p>The whole of the island of Martinique and Fort de France are threatened. In order
                    to enable us to save the population you will please ask, as a national service,
                    of the American Government that it may see fit to send means of transportation
                    to Martinique (Fort de France) as soon as possible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Delcassé.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
